# Roles

- `patient`
- `psychologist`
- `practice_manager`
- `admin`

# Access Rules

- Public routes do not require authentication.
- Auth routes (`/login`, `/register`, reset flows) are guest-only.
- Protected routes require explicit allowed roles.
- Shared routes must explicitly list all allowed roles.
- Do not assume manager/admin equivalence unless route config states both.

# Default Deny

- Any role not explicitly allowed for a protected route is denied.

# Change Protocol

When route access changes:
1. Update route guard configuration in `src/routes/AppRoutes.tsx`.
2. Update `docs/role-matrix.md`.
3. Update `docs/routes-overview.md` if route mapping changed.
